    "Classic": {
      "mulligan": {
        "info": "If your starting hand contains no partner cards, you are able to redraw. You must show your opponent your hand to show you have no partner cards, and then return your hand to your deck, shuffle it, and draw 6 cards. If you still have no partner card after redrawing, you may try again. Your starting hand will contain one less card for every time you redraw.  Thus, if you don't have a partner card in your starting hand, you can redraw up to 6 times. Of course, as a strategy, you can start the game without redrawing. In this case, you do not need to show your opponent your hand.  ‚óèWhat if I run out of cards?  If your deck runs out of cards, you don't immediately lose.  The game will continue without you drawing a card. Without having cards to draw you will be at a disadvantage, but victory is not impossible. Depending on the situation, it's entirely possible to win.",
